# Inventory Logic Fixes Walkthrough

We have successfully audited and patched critical vulnerabilities in the inventory management system.

## Key Changes

### 1. Stock Duplication Fix ([lib/inventoryService.ts](file:///c:/Users/USUARIO/Desktop/proyectos/servitelv/web/lib/inventoryService.ts))
**Problem**: When a user corrected an order (deleted a used item), the system returned the material to the Crew's bobbin BUT also credited the Main Warehouse, effectively creating duplicate stock out of thin air.
**Fix**: Added logic to [restoreInventoryFromOrder](file:///c:/Users/USUARIO/Desktop/proyectos/servitelv/web/lib/inventoryService.ts#690-913) to check where the bobbin is located.
```typescript
// ONLY credit warehouse if the batch is physically there
if (batch.location === 'warehouse') {
    await InventoryModel.findByIdAndUpdate(..., { $inc: { currentStock: ... } });
}
```

### 2. Strict Meter Validation
**Problem**: It was possible to add "meters" of cable directly to the inventory without creating a Bobbin, leading to untrackable cable stock.
**Fix**: Updated [restockInventory](file:///c:/Users/USUARIO/Desktop/proyectos/servitelv/web/lib/inventoryService.ts#14-96) to block any attempt to add stock to items measured in "metros".
```typescript
if (inventoryItem.unit === "metros") {
    throw new Error("El ítem... se mide en metros y debe ingresarse como Bobina");
}
```

## Verification
- **Restoration**: Restoring an item now correctly updates the local batch/crew inventory without inflating the global warehouse assets.
- **Data Integrity**: New constraints ensure all cable inventory exists within a verifiable Batch/Bobbin.
